\key{Retreat}: When retreating using your movement rate, your
opponents can follow you and continue to attack unless somebody is
covering your retreat. If you need to move faster, you'll have to
flee.

\key{Flee}: When running away, you'll have to survive one last round
of attacks. All your opponents in melee get one free attack with a +2
bonus.\marginnote[-4em]{Everybody in melee gets exactly \emph{one}
  extra attack against fleeing opponents. If you didn't use a melee
  weapon, you're not in melee and don't get to make an extra attack.}

