\key{Conditions}: The \emph{Death \& Dismemberment} table imposes
various conditions:

\textbf{Arm Lost or Broken}: You can retrain your sword hand, no
problem. You'll need a hand to cast spells.\marginnote{ If you loose
  both arms, you'll need to get yourself a new arm. A mechanical arm
  made by gnomes will do, if you'll trust them not to pull a prank on
  you.}

\textbf{Leg Lost or Broken}: You can't walk until you get yourself a
wooden leg. You'll never run using a wooden leg.\marginnote{If you
  loose both legs, you'll need to find somebody to carry you or
  magical means of movement.}

\textbf{Rib Broken}: No sudden moves with a broken rib or you'll
pierce your lung!

\key{Helpless}: you can be killed without requiring a roll to hit.

\key{Stunned}: you cannot move and you cannot attack, but opponents
must still roll to hit.

\key{Knocked Down}: opponents get +4 to hit you until you get up;
getting up prevents you from moving in the same round.

