\key{Help}: The help of towns and factions may depend on your
reputation. Roll 2d6 and compare it to your reputation. If you rolled
\emph{higher}, help is not forthcoming.

\key[Intervention]{Intervention}: In an emergency, reputation also
acts as the percentage chance for divine intervention.\marginnote{A
  divine intervention could mean the appearance of an angel, a devil,
  demon, a naga, or the like.}

\key[Miracles!Reputation]{Miracles}: Reputation also limits the circle
of miracles available to clerics. Thus, a cleric cannot work any
miracles on their first adventure since they are lacking an
appropriate reputation. You need to gain a reputation of 1 in order to
work miracles of the first circle.

