\section{\index{Spells}Spells of Magic Users and Elves}
\label{sec:spells}

Magic users and elves begin their career with exactly \emph{one} spell
in their spell book. When you gain a level, you can learn one or more
new spells from your peers. The referee will have at least one source
of new spells prepared.\marginnote{Magic users and elves will often
  stay close to their former master and keep learning new spells from
  them, often in exchange for services rendered. This is why many low
  level casters will simply have a subset of their master's spell
  book.
  
  An alternative to that is \key{Research}. This requires a starting
  point such as an existing a scroll, spell book or magic item, and a
  library of further books about the origins of magic, related spells,
  history and lore, and so on. The magic user or elf must have
  attained level~9 and spend 1,000 gold and two weeks per spell level
  researching (no adventuring).

  \bigskip The table determines both the number of spells you can cast
  \emph{per day} and the number of spells \emph{in your repertoire}.}

\key[Repertoire!Magic Users and Elves]{Repertoire}: The list of spells
in your spell book make up your repertoire. When casting a spell,
choose a spell from your repertoire. The size of your repertoire is
determined by your level:

\medskip
\begin{tabular}{cccccc}
Level & 1\st circle & 2\nd circle & 3\rd circle & 4\th circle & 5\th circle \\
1 & 1 & - & - & - & - \\
2 & 2 & - & - & - & - \\
3 & 2 & 1 & - & - & - \\
4 & 2 & 2 & - & - & - \\
5 & 2 & 2 & 1 & - & - \\
6 & 2 & 2 & 2 & - & - \\
7 & 3 & 2 & 2 & 1 & - \\
8 & 3 & 3 & 2 & 2 & - \\
9 & 3 & 3 & 3 & 2 & 1 \\
10 & 3 & 3 & 3 & 3 & 2 \\
\end{tabular}

\newthought{On 1\st level you start} with a single spell from your
master's spell book. Typically, \hyperref[sec:candidates]{retainers}
would have one of the following:

\textbf{Charm Person} turns \emph{one} humanoid creature into a loyal
friend. The target is granted a saving throw
vs.~spells.\marginnote{Undead and giants may be humanoid but they're
  still immune to this charm.} As time passes, more saving throws are
granted to the target:

\medskip
\begin{tabular}{cl}
Intelligence & Timeframe \\
3--8 & monthly \\
9--12 & weekly \\
13--18 & daily \\
\end{tabular}
\medskip

\textbf{Detect Magic} makes all enchanted items, creatures and
locations within \emph{\unit[60]{ft}} shine with a pale blue light for
\emph{\unit[20]{min}}.\marginnote[-1em]{The pale blue light is visible
  to all.}

\textbf{Light} enchants one object within \emph{\unit[120]{ft}} for
\emph{\unit[1]{h} + \unit[10]{min/level}} so that it shines faint
light with a \emph{\unit[15]{ft}} radius.\marginnote[-2em]{If you target the
  eyes of a creature, it will go blind for as long as the spell lasts.
  Blind creatures are at -4 to hit. Targets are granted a saving throw
  vs.~spells.}

\textbf{Magic Missile} hits any target within \emph{\unit[150]{ft}}
and causes 1W6+1 damage. At 5\th level, \emph{three} missiles can be
shot at the same time and they hit different targets.\marginnote{There
  is no saving throw!}

\textbf{Read Magic} allows you to decipher magical runes for
\emph{\unit[10]{min}}. This is how to read spell books, scrolls and
magical inscriptions.

\textbf{Sleep} puts \emph{2W8 hit dice} of creatures within
\emph{\unit[240]{ft}} to sleep for \emph{4W4 $\times$ \unit[10]{min}}.
This is a magical slumber. They need to be slapped in order to wake
them before the spell ends. No creature may have more than 4+1~hit
dice. Creatures with less hit dice are affected
first.\marginnote{There is no saving throw!}

